
  Name:  frexp
 
  #include <math.h>
  float frexpf(float num, int *exp);
  double frexp(double num, int *exp);
  long double frexpl(long double num, int *exp);

  The frexp( ) family of functions decomposes the number num into
  a mantissa in the range 0.5 to less than 1
  
  Example:
  int e;
  double f;
  f = frexp(10.0, &e);
  printf(''%f %d", f, e);

  Related Function:  ldexp

